        "title": "Post: Chat",
        "excerpt":"Abbott: Strange as it may seem, they give ball players nowadays very peculiar names.Costello: Funny names?Abbott: Nicknames, nicknames. Now, on the St. Louis team we have Who‚Äôs on first, What‚Äôs on second, I Don‚Äôt Know is on third‚ÄìCostello: That‚Äôs what I want to find out. I want you to tell me the names of the fellows on the St. Louis team.Abbott: I‚Äôm telling you. Who‚Äôs on first, What‚Äôs on second, I Don‚Äôt Know is on third‚ÄìCostello: You know the fellows‚Äô names?Abbott: Yes.Costello: Well, then who‚Äôs playing first?Abbott: Yes.Costello: I mean the fellow‚Äôs name on first base.Abbott: Who.Costello: The fellow playin‚Äô first base.Abbott: Who.Costello: The guy on first base.Abbott: Who is on first.Costello: Well, what are you askin‚Äô me for?Abbott: I‚Äôm not asking you‚ÄìI‚Äôm telling you. Who is on first.Costello: I‚Äôm asking you‚Äìwho‚Äôs on first?Abbott: That‚Äôs the man‚Äôs name.Costello: That‚Äôs who‚Äôs name?Abbott: Yes.Costello: When you pay off the first baseman every month, who gets the money?Abbott: Every dollar of it. And why not, the man‚Äôs entitled to it.Costello: Who is?Abbott: Yes.Costello: So who gets it?Abbott: Why shouldn‚Äôt he? Sometimes his wife comes down and collects it.Costello: Who‚Äôs wife?Abbott: Yes. After all, the man earns it.Costello: Who does?Abbott: Absolutely.Costello: Well, all I‚Äôm trying to find out is what‚Äôs the guy‚Äôs name on first base?Abbott: Oh, no, no. What is on second base.Costello: I‚Äôm not asking you who‚Äôs on second.Abbott: Who‚Äôs on first!Costello: St. Louis has a good outfield?Abbott: Oh, absolutely.Costello: The left fielder‚Äôs name?Abbott: Why.Costello: I don‚Äôt know, I just thought I‚Äôd ask.Abbott: Well, I just thought I‚Äôd tell you.Costello: Then tell me who‚Äôs playing left field?Abbott: Who‚Äôs playing first.Costello: Stay out of the infield! The left fielder‚Äôs name?Abbott: Why.Costello: Because.Abbott: Oh, he‚Äôs center field.Costello: Wait a minute. You got a pitcher on this team?Abbott: Wouldn‚Äôt this be a fine team without a pitcher?Costello: Tell me the pitcher‚Äôs name.Abbott: Tomorrow.Costello: Now, when the guy at bat bunts the ball‚Äìme being a good catcher‚ÄìI want to throw the guy out at first base, so I pick up the ball and throw it to who?Abbott: Now, that‚Äôs he first thing you‚Äôve said right.Costello: I DON‚ÄôT EVEN KNOW WHAT I‚ÄôM TALKING ABOUT!Abbott: Don‚Äôt get excited. Take it easy.Costello: I throw the ball to first base, whoever it is grabs the ball, so the guy runs to second. Who picks up the ball and throws it to what. What throws it to I don‚Äôt know. I don‚Äôt know throws it back to tomorrow‚Äìa triple play.Abbott: Yeah, it could be.Costello: Another guy gets up and it‚Äôs a long ball to center.Abbott: Because.Costello: Why? I don‚Äôt know. And I don‚Äôt care.Abbott: What was that?Costello: I said, I DON‚ÄôT CARE!Abbott: Oh, that‚Äôs our shortstop!","categories": ["Post Formats"],
